Adjust rack to top position and preheat #oven{} to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all produce. Dice @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch pieces (no need to peel). If necessary, cut @Broccoli Florets{8%ounce} into 1-inch pieces. Mince @Chives{¼%ounce}.

Place potatoes in a large #pot{} with enough @salt{}ed water to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil and cook until very tender, ~{15-20%minutes}. Reserve ½ cup potato cooking liquid, then drain. Return potatoes to pot and add @Sour Cream{2%tablespoon}, half the chives, and @Butter{1%tablespoon}. Mash with a #potato masher{}, adding splashes of reserved cooking liquid as needed, until smooth and creamy; season with salt and @Pepper{}. Cover to keep warm.

While potatoes cook, toss broccoli on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @Olive Oil{2%teaspoon}, salt, and pepper. Roast, tossing halfway through, until browned and slightly crispy, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Meanwhile, pat @Beef Tenderloin Filets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with salt and pepper. Heat a drizzle of @Vegetable Oil{1%teaspoon} in a large #pan{} over medium-high heat. Add beef and cook until a crust begins to form, ~{4-7%minutes} per side. Remove from heat; set beef aside to rest. Wipe out pan.

Add half the @Balsamic Vinegar{5%teaspoon} (use the rest however you like), @Beef Demi-Glace{1%unit}, and @water{¼%cup} to same pan over medium-high heat. Bring to a simmer and cook until thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Remove from heat and stir in @Butter{1%tablespoon} until melted. Season with salt and pepper.

Divide beef, broccoli, and potatoes between plates. Drizzle beef with sauce. Garnish with remaining chives.